title: High Foreign Direct Investment Outflows
description: In 2023, the Netherlands experienced a significant net outflow of foreign direct investment, totaling approximately $332.5 billion, indicating a substantial capital movement out of the country.

title: Minimal PM2.5 Pollution Exposure
description: As of 2017, only 0.04% of the Dutch population was exposed to PM2.5 pollution levels exceeding the WHO's Interim Target-3, showcasing effective air quality management.

title: Universal Financial Account Ownership Among Older Adults
description: By 2021, 100% of the Dutch population aged 25 and older owned an account at a financial institution or with a mobile-money-service provider, reflecting widespread financial inclusion.

title: High Employment Rates for Young Females
description: In 2024, the employment to population ratio for Dutch females aged 15-24 was 76.53%, indicating robust job opportunities for young women.

title: High Employment Rates for Young Males
description: The employment to population ratio for Dutch males aged 15-24 reached 76.76% in 2024, reflecting strong labor market participation among young men.

title: Strong Youth Employment
description: In 2024, the Netherlands boasted a total employment to population ratio of 76.65% for individuals aged 15-24, highlighting a healthy youth labor market.

title: High Female Labor Force Participation
description: The labor force participation rate for Dutch females aged 15-24 was 83.08% in 2024, indicating high engagement in the workforce.

title: High Male Labor Force Participation
description: In 2024, the labor force participation rate for Dutch males aged 15-24 was 83.83%, showcasing strong workforce involvement.

title: Robust Youth Labor Force Participation
description: The Netherlands had a total labor force participation rate of 83.46% for individuals aged 15-24 in 2024, reflecting a vibrant youth workforce.
